    "Since we do not know but only forecast the bid-ask spread, volatility, and volume, which appear in the transaction cost (10) (which is itself only an approximation) we should consider the post-trade cash c in (7) as an approximation that uses a forecast of holding and transaction costs, not the realized holding and transaction costs.",
